pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `employees` ( `id` bigint(20) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `department_id` bigint(20) unsigned NOT NULL, `name` varchar(255) COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci NOT NULL, `date_of_birth` date NOT NULL, `position` varchar(255) COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci NOT NULL, `type_of_employee` enum('rate','hourly wage') COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci NOT NULL, `monthly_pay` double NOT NULL, `created_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT NULL, `updated_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`), KEY `employees_department_id_foreign` (`department_id`), CONSTRAINT `employees_department_id_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`department_id`) REFERENCES `departments` (`id`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=101 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
